<section class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-3xl">
      Skills are load-bearing now. Nothing is holding them up.
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-5 text-ink-dim leading-relaxed">
      Your agent skills review code, write commits, summarize incidents —
      real work rides on them. But a SKILL.md is a paste of unknown
      pedigree: nobody remembers why it&#39;s shaped the way it is, nothing
      tells you when a model update quietly breaks it, and &ldquo;it seemed
      to work&rdquo; is the entire test suite. The teams who feel this
      hand-roll their own eval CI. Everyone else finds out in production.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-4 text-ink leading-relaxed">
      Skillmaker exists so a skill can carry its own evidence — who
      designed it and why, what it was tested against, how it scored —
      pinned to the exact version and model that earned the numbers.
    </p>
  </div>
